# ============================================================
# .DOCKERIGNORE
# ============================================================
# Works exactly like .gitignore but for Docker.
# When Docker builds an image, it sends the entire project
# directory to the Docker daemon as "build context."
# This file tells Docker to SKIP files that aren't needed,
# making builds faster and images smaller.
# ============================================================

# .NET build artifacts (we rebuild inside the container)
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/out/
# Catch directories with literal backslashes (created by some Windows tools on macOS)
**/bin\*
**/obj\*
# Stale publish output
**/publish/
**/deploy.zip

# Node modules (we run npm ci inside the container)
**/node_modules/

# Angular build output (we rebuild inside the container)
**/dist/
**/.angular/

# IDE and OS files
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Git
**/.git/
**/.gitignore

# Docker files (no need to copy Docker into Docker)
**/Dockerfile
**/Dockerfile.*
**/docker-compose.yml
**/.dockerignore

# Secrets and local config (NEVER put secrets in a Docker image)
**/secrets.json
**/*.user

# Documentation and misc
**/*.md
**/LICENSE
**/repomix-output.xml